      "content": "hey so im working on this embedded c++ project for an automotive controller and im hitting a wall. the system has like 512mb of ram and after running the main loop for about 4 or 5 hours the heap is just totally exhausted. i've checked the obvious stuff but i cant find the culprit. \n\ncan u give me a systematic way to hunt down where the memory is leaking? here is the main loop logic:\n\n```cpp\nvoid process_sensor_data(SensorData* data) {\n    if (data != nullptr) {\n        TelemetryPacket* packet = new TelemetryPacket(data);\n        log_buffer.push_back(packet);\n        if (log_buffer.size() > MAX_LOG_SIZE) {\n            // logic to prune logs...\n            delete log_buffer.front();\n            log_buffer.erase(log_buffer.begin());\n        }\n        transmit_packet(packet);\n    }\n}\n```\nit looks okay at first glance but the leak is definitely real. what should i look for next?",
      "source": "evaluator"
